  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "I've noticed this during writing IPC tests, that Windows named pipes produce all kinds of weird error messages: `Access Denied`, `EOF` among others. The first one appeared when I tried to reuse the same pipe path between tests (properly closed in between). The second error appeared when I ran tests that started up an IPC endpoint and immediately connected a`jsre` to it. If I wait 100ms after creating the pipe everything works fine. It seems that there are some timing issues / race condition with Windows named pipes where Windows returns execution to us, but the pipe itself is not yet prepared, leading to some very odd errors. I've added a 100ms delay inside the `node` after opening the IPC channel on Windows until we can figure out the real solution.\n",
